      "body" : "Added a commit that uses LogPrintf + abort() in case of randomness failure. Adding the ability to install an error handler seems reasonable, but doing it correctly would require locking primitives~~, which would cause libconsensus to end up depending on boost again~~. After the C++11 switchover this will be much easier, and I'd prefer to do that in a separate PR then.\r\n\r\nEDIT: I'm wrong, libconsensus does not depend on random. Still, can we keep error handling for another PR?",
